Part B: Prevention Reflection

The most surprising thing I discovered while researching this topic was the psychological pressure scammers use. They don't just send a link; they create a sense of extreme urgency—claiming a bank account will be blocked or a "limited-time" refund will expire—to stop the victim from thinking clearly. I was also surprised to learn how often scammers use "mule accounts" to bounce the stolen money through several layers within minutes.

As a result, the one habit I will personally change is enabling transaction limits on my UPI app. By setting a daily cap on how much can be transferred, I can mitigate the potential damage even if a security lapse occurs. Additionally, I have committed to never answering "Collect Requests" from unknown IDs, regardless of the story provided by the sender
